===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|color|colo(u)r|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|colur|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|colour|lang=fro}}, {{term|color|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|color|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|OL.}} ''[[colos]]'' "covering", from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|kel-||to cover, conceal|lang=ine-pro}}. Akin to Latin {{term|celo|cēlō|I hide, conceal|lang=la}}. Displaced [[Middle English]] {{term|blee||colour|lang=enm}}, from Old English {{term|bleo|blēo|lang=ang}}. More at [[blee]].

In the US, the spelling ''color'' is used to match the spelling of the word's Latin etymon{{,}} and to make all derivatives consistent (''colorimeter'', ''colorize'', ''colorless'', etc). Elsewhere in the English-speaking world, the spelling ''colour'' has been retained.

